        <h2 class="mb-4">1. What is Cocaine?</h2>
        <p>
            Cocaine is a powerful stimulant drug derived from the leaves of the coca plant. It affects the central nervous system, producing intense feelings of energy, alertness, and euphoria. In the United States, cocaine is classified as an illegal substance due to its high potential for abuse and addiction.
        </p>
        <p>
            It is commonly found in two forms:
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li>Powder cocaine (snorted or injected)</li>
            <li>Crack cocaine (smoked)</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
