        <h2 class="mb-4">3. Legal Status in the USA</h2>
        <p>
            Cocaine is classified as a Schedule II drug under U.S. federal law. While it has limited medical use in specific clinical settings, recreational use is illegal. Possession, distribution, and trafficking can result in severe legal penalties.
        </p>

        <p>
            Legal consequences may include:
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li>Fines and imprisonment</li>
            <li>Criminal records</li>
            <li>Long-term social and economic impacts</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
</section>

