        <p>
            Cocaine addiction remains a significant public health issue in the United States. It affects individuals across different age groups and socioeconomic backgrounds.
        </p>

        <p>
            Key concerns include:
        </p>

        <ul>
            <li>High risk of overdose</li>
            <li>Increased emergency room visits</li>
            <li>Strain on healthcare systems</li>
            <li>Connection to other substance abuse disorders</li>
        </ul>

        <p>
            Treatment options such as behavioral therapy, counseling, and rehabilitation programs are commonly used to help individuals recover.
        </p>
    </div>
</section>

